============================================================
12) Publishing Workflow and Roles
============================================================
Role Map:
- Content Owner: drafts post and media.
- Technical Reviewer: validates claims and metrics.
- Brand Reviewer: consistency and readability.
- Publisher: publishes and schedules comments.
- Analyst: reports weekly KPI dashboard.

Workflow SLA:
- Draft D-2 days
- Technical review D-1 day
- Publish day D
- First-comment optimization within 10 minutes
- 24h/72h performance check-ins

============================================================
13) Post-Publish Optimization SOP
============================================================
Within 15 minutes:
- Add first comment with key link/CTA.
- Team members provide first wave of meaningful engagement.

Within 24 hours:
- Respond to all relevant comments.
- Pin best technical reply if useful.

Within 72 hours:
- Log KPIs, compare to benchmark, label winning variant.
- Feed insights into next week content plan.

============================================================
14) Risk Controls
============================================================
- Do not publish unverifiable performance claims.
- Avoid confidential customer/project references.
- Keep security discussions accurate and non-sensitive.
- Ensure legal-safe language around compliance and cryptography.

============================================================
15) Execution Checklist (Per Post)
============================================================
[ ] Hook selected from tested winner set
[ ] One clear CTA
[ ] UTM-tagged link generated
[ ] Technical claims reviewed
[ ] Visual asset quality checked
[ ] Hashtags selected (3-5 max)
[ ] First comment prepared
[ ] KPI logging slot prepared
[ ] Pre-publish screenshots captured and archived
[ ] Day-1 and Day-3 analytics screenshots scheduled
[ ] Technical proof screenshot added (CI/architecture/feature)
[ ] Redaction and readability check completed

